1
00:00:02,413 --> 00:00:04,113
"Episode 7"

2
00:00:12,849 --> 00:00:15,324
What is this uncomfortable silence?

3
00:00:18,801 --> 00:00:21,652
Wow, it's such a clear day!

4
00:00:21,732 --> 00:00:22,754
Please close the window,
I prefer silence.

5
00:00:22,834 --> 00:00:25,615
Yes. We'll go in silence.

6
00:00:30,201 --> 00:00:32,366
Wow, these are cool sunglasses!

7
00:00:32,446 --> 00:00:33,652
You're going to get smudges on them.

8
00:00:33,732 --> 00:00:35,965
I know. We don't want any smudges.

9
00:00:42,938 --> 00:00:44,738
I'll take over the wheel
at the next rest stop.

10
00:00:44,818 --> 00:00:46,650
I'm not planning to make any stops.

11
00:00:46,730 --> 00:00:48,793
I think we should
head directly there as well.

12
00:00:58,317 --> 00:00:59,597
Do you think this is a vacation?

13
00:01:00,820 --> 00:01:01,665
No.

14
00:01:01,745 --> 00:01:04,744
I've got a lot of things on my mind,
so can we go quietly?

15
00:01:04,824 --> 00:01:05,733
Sure.

16
00:01:11,052 --> 00:01:13,454
I'm trying to be quiet,
but I'm having trouble controlling it.

17
00:01:13,534 --> 00:01:15,988
What's this?
Why does he have to be so cold?

18
00:01:16,275 --> 00:01:18,796
If you were going to be this way,
why did you give me the onion?

19
00:01:32,186 --> 00:01:33,210
What?

20
00:01:35,278 --> 00:01:36,349
Never mind.

21
00:01:37,359 --> 00:01:38,585
Please carry on.

22
00:01:39,372 --> 00:01:40,537
Please take a look at this...

23
00:01:40,617 --> 00:01:43,126
-Hey!
-I've seen it already.

24
00:01:43,206 --> 00:01:44,840
When is Kim Shinhyuk going to grow up?

25
00:01:44,920 --> 00:01:45,888
Probably never.

26
00:01:46,472 --> 00:01:48,832
No one gives a reaction
quite like Jackson.

27
00:01:54,220 --> 00:01:55,463
Jackson...

28
00:02:10,172 --> 00:02:12,359
Wow, this air is so fresh!

29
00:02:15,193 --> 00:02:17,678
Why don't we fill ourselves with food
instead of air?

30
00:02:17,758 --> 00:02:18,761
Okay.

31
00:02:21,764 --> 00:02:23,778
-How do you do?
-Hello.

32
00:02:23,858 --> 00:02:25,868
Would you like to order?
What would you like?

33
00:02:25,948 --> 00:02:27,094
I'll have the vegetable bibimbap.

34
00:02:27,174 --> 00:02:28,472
We'll have two tenderloin specials.

35
00:02:28,552 --> 00:02:29,708
No, I want the vegetable.

36
00:02:32,662 --> 00:02:34,626
Isn't that too expensive?

37
00:02:34,706 --> 00:02:36,060
Do you have a problem with the price...

38
00:02:36,140 --> 00:02:37,787
...when I'm the one who's paying?

39
00:02:37,867 --> 00:02:42,388
You should really try our raw meat plate.

40
00:02:42,823 --> 00:02:47,022
It's direct from the farm,
so the meat is really fresh.

41
00:02:47,102 --> 00:02:48,422
We'll take an order of that, too.

42
00:02:48,696 --> 00:02:49,869
Sure!

43
00:02:50,413 --> 00:02:53,133
Two tenderloin specials
and one raw meat platter!

44
00:02:54,927 --> 00:02:56,226
It's so expensive!

45
00:02:56,633 --> 00:02:58,807
I think it's going to be too much.

46
00:02:58,887 --> 00:03:01,267
I'm not going to ask you to pay,
so don't worry about it.

47
00:03:02,401 --> 00:03:03,942
I already told you that it's on me.

48
00:03:09,721 --> 00:03:12,634
Who left their wallet here like this?

49
00:03:13,197 --> 00:03:16,259
They went together,
so it should be all right.

50
00:03:19,107 --> 00:03:20,427
Maybe he left it here on purpose?

51
00:03:21,091 --> 00:03:22,007
That's smart.

52
00:03:25,438 --> 00:03:28,774
The meat that we bring in are fresh...

53
00:03:29,036 --> 00:03:31,380
...and of top quality.

54
00:03:32,182 --> 00:03:33,583
It practically melts in your mouth.

55
00:03:33,973 --> 00:03:34,987
Is it done yet?

56
00:03:38,908 --> 00:03:40,276
It's to die for!

57
00:03:40,356 --> 00:03:41,748
My goodness.

58
00:03:42,583 --> 00:03:44,244
Sorry about the grease.

59
00:03:44,640 --> 00:03:46,465
Would you like an apron?

60
00:03:47,951 --> 00:03:49,153
Aren't you going to wear one?

61
00:03:49,233 --> 00:03:50,959
I don't care about my clothes.

62
00:03:51,258 --> 00:03:52,712
Oh, right... My employee badge.

63
00:03:52,792 --> 00:03:54,376
I don't want this to get dirty.

64
00:03:54,560 --> 00:03:55,986
Are you dating the badge?

65
00:03:56,066 --> 00:03:58,066
Why must you wear
that on a business trip?

66
00:03:58,623 --> 00:04:00,860
This is my greatest possession.

67
00:04:01,210 --> 00:04:04,018
Simply wearing it gives me strength.

68
00:04:09,421 --> 00:04:12,321
I don't know
how I should interpret that scoff.

69
00:04:12,401 --> 00:04:13,374
Oh, no.

70
00:04:14,063 --> 00:04:16,312
That seems awfully provocative.

71
00:04:18,956 --> 00:04:21,644
If you take it off,
you'll get grease on your clothes.

72
00:04:23,095 --> 00:04:24,067
Let's eat.

73
00:04:31,857 --> 00:04:33,218
What do you keep looking at?

74
00:04:39,272 --> 00:04:40,788
Quit staring at me.

75
00:04:51,153 --> 00:04:53,166
I'm sorry.

76
00:04:57,075 --> 00:04:58,079
What the...

77
00:04:58,488 --> 00:05:00,220
You've had a feast.

78
00:05:02,598 --> 00:05:04,576
That will be 185 dollars.

79
00:05:04,737 --> 00:05:05,680
Yes.

80
00:05:12,172 --> 00:05:14,246
It's 185 dollars.

81
00:05:15,395 --> 00:05:16,341
Sure.

82
00:05:19,561 --> 00:05:22,832
185 dollars!

83
00:05:33,102 --> 00:05:34,744
I already told you
that I'm paying for it.

84
00:05:44,711 --> 00:05:46,638
Thank you for the meal!

85
00:05:46,934 --> 00:05:49,627
That was the best meat I've ever tasted!

86
00:05:57,755 --> 00:05:58,787
Well...

87
00:06:01,946 --> 00:06:03,187
Let me borrow some...

88
00:06:05,189 --> 00:06:07,806
What did you say? I couldn't hear
because of that motorcycle.

89
00:06:09,930 --> 00:06:11,928
I left it back at the office,

90
00:06:13,957 --> 00:06:14,962
my wallet.

91
00:06:15,836 --> 00:06:18,081
Let me use your card
during the business trip.

92
00:06:20,865 --> 00:06:22,981
Is there something wrong
with this machine?

93
00:06:25,521 --> 00:06:26,983
You don't have enough balance.

94
00:06:27,063 --> 00:06:28,807
You're short 40 dollars.

95
00:06:28,887 --> 00:06:29,959
Really?

96
00:06:30,882 --> 00:06:32,230
What should I do?

97
00:06:32,980 --> 00:06:37,142
We can pay you when
the rest of our team gets here.

98
00:06:37,222 --> 00:06:38,267
What?

99
00:06:38,703 --> 00:06:40,908
So you can skip out on your tab?

100
00:06:41,574 --> 00:06:43,178
We're not those kinds of people.

101
00:06:44,039 --> 00:06:46,636
Then I can leave you with my ID.

102
00:06:46,716 --> 00:06:49,264
My goodness. Unbelievable.

103
00:06:49,445 --> 00:06:51,254
I'll leave this as collateral,

104
00:06:51,334 --> 00:06:53,495
and when our people arrive,
we'll come back to pay you.

105
00:06:55,782 --> 00:06:57,653
I won't put up with this!

106
00:06:57,733 --> 00:06:59,631
I have a truckload of these!

107
00:06:59,888 --> 00:07:01,892
These are worth a dollar!

108
00:07:01,972 --> 00:07:03,226
Give me my 40 dollars.

109
00:07:03,306 --> 00:07:04,766
This isn't worth a dollar.

110
00:07:04,846 --> 00:07:06,421
This is part of
the 2015 FW Paris collection.

111
00:07:06,501 --> 00:07:11,214
I don't care where it's from!

112
00:07:11,294 --> 00:07:12,339
This won't do.

113
00:07:12,419 --> 00:07:14,281
Honey, call the police.

114
00:07:17,159 --> 00:07:20,082
We've got a problem here!
These people are crazy!

115
00:07:20,739 --> 00:07:22,010
I can't believe they're ripping me off!

116
00:07:22,090 --> 00:07:23,893
How far are you?

117
00:07:23,973 --> 00:07:26,381
We're passing Daejeon now.

118
00:07:26,544 --> 00:07:27,531
Daejeon?

119
00:07:27,855 --> 00:07:29,859
Why are you in Daejeon when you're
supposed to head to Kangwon Province?

120
00:07:29,939 --> 00:07:31,060
It's the opposite direction.

121
00:07:31,664 --> 00:07:33,627
Oh, my, what am I going to do?

122
00:07:33,707 --> 00:07:36,309
I thought it was
in the Kyungsang Province!

123
00:07:36,389 --> 00:07:39,409
So it's Kangwon Province?

124
00:07:39,955 --> 00:07:41,700
What am I going to do?

125
00:07:41,780 --> 00:07:43,925
Yes, I'll turn the car around right away.

126
00:07:46,080 --> 00:07:47,703
Why? Is something wrong?

127
00:07:47,783 --> 00:07:50,796
We're supposed to be in Kangwon Province,
not Kyungsang.

128
00:07:50,876 --> 00:07:52,064
I had no idea.

129
00:07:53,363 --> 00:07:54,319
What?

130
00:07:54,564 --> 00:07:56,508
How can you make that kind of mistake?

131
00:07:58,400 --> 00:08:00,281
How long will it take us
to get there from here?

132
00:08:05,806 --> 00:08:06,905
Call the police.

133
00:08:06,985 --> 00:08:08,128
Wait, hold on.

134
00:08:08,396 --> 00:08:11,792
I'll call my friend
and tell her to wire the money.

135
00:08:23,746 --> 00:08:25,519
Why isn't she picking up?

136
00:08:25,834 --> 00:08:26,743
She's not picking up?

137
00:08:28,332 --> 00:08:31,747
Are you sure it's not on purpose?

138
00:08:32,722 --> 00:08:35,886
Don't pull any funny business,
and give the phone to me when she does.

139
00:08:35,966 --> 00:08:36,948
Okay.

140
00:08:38,712 --> 00:08:42,156
Can you call someone
and ask them to send you some money?

141
00:08:43,355 --> 00:08:45,719
I don't have anyone I can call.

142
00:08:46,747 --> 00:08:48,041
Not a single person?

143
00:08:48,883 --> 00:08:49,969
No one.

144
00:08:50,513 --> 00:08:52,184
How can you not know a single person?

145
00:08:58,034 --> 00:09:00,115
I'm going crazy!

146
00:09:07,245 --> 00:09:09,148
That's Shinhyuk's phone.
I wonder where he is?

147
00:09:09,789 --> 00:09:11,458
He's in a meeting with Photographer Kang.

148
00:09:11,838 --> 00:09:12,920
Gosh.

149
00:09:17,305 --> 00:09:18,808
Isn't Jackson supposed to be Hyejin?

150
00:09:20,472 --> 00:09:21,532
Yes, Hyejin.

151
00:09:21,828 --> 00:09:23,315
Hello?

152
00:09:23,652 --> 00:09:25,466
Yes, hello!

153
00:09:25,870 --> 00:09:27,699
Are you acquaintances with a Kim Hyejin?

154
00:09:27,779 --> 00:09:28,997
Who is this?

155
00:09:29,077 --> 00:09:33,011
Yes, Kim Hyejin needs to pay her tab...

156
00:09:33,091 --> 00:09:34,933
...but her card has been declined.

157
00:09:35,263 --> 00:09:39,754
Please send money
to her account for her tab.

158
00:09:40,833 --> 00:09:42,038
Look here, Lady.

159
00:09:42,706 --> 00:09:44,289
This is rather awkward.

160
00:09:44,823 --> 00:09:47,005
How are you going to
make a living with that script?

161
00:09:47,085 --> 00:09:51,938
Practise your pitch
and try again later, okay?

162
00:09:53,867 --> 00:09:55,064
What a joke.

163
00:09:56,927 --> 00:09:58,852
No one pick up Hyejin's calls.

164
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:00,651
Why, Ms Cha?

165
00:10:02,026 --> 00:10:04,268
I can't believe that they're
phishing through cell phones now.

166
00:10:04,348 --> 00:10:06,108
It was a voice phishing attempt
from Hyejin's number.

167
00:10:06,188 --> 00:10:07,540
I can tell it's fake.

168
00:10:08,161 --> 00:10:10,224
Really? Oh, my!

169
00:10:10,304 --> 00:10:12,379
I'm getting the same call!

170
00:10:13,532 --> 00:10:14,749
Don't pick it up, Ms Joo.

171
00:10:15,511 --> 00:10:16,642
I'm not falling for this.

172
00:10:17,053 --> 00:10:18,342
Beat it, you phisher!

173
00:10:18,756 --> 00:10:20,203
Why isn't anyone picking up?

174
00:10:20,637 --> 00:10:21,788
Gosh.

175
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:27,443
What should we do?

176
00:10:27,661 --> 00:10:29,234
What else can you do?

177
00:10:29,314 --> 00:10:31,296
You'll need to work off the rest.

178
00:10:40,305 --> 00:10:42,295
Change into this. This is your uniform.

179
00:10:44,375 --> 00:10:46,464
I don't know what you want us to do...

180
00:10:46,950 --> 00:10:48,458
...but I'm not going to wear this.

181
00:10:49,251 --> 00:10:50,584
Change into it.

182
00:11:00,822 --> 00:11:01,811
Take a look.

183
00:11:01,891 --> 00:11:03,381
This is my farm.

184
00:11:06,846 --> 00:11:08,937
I want you to clean the cow manure,
40 dollars' worth.

185
00:11:09,017 --> 00:11:09,974
What?

186
00:11:10,246 --> 00:11:11,569
You want us to scoop cow poop?

187
00:11:11,649 --> 00:11:13,798
How can you expect us to do that?

188
00:11:15,917 --> 00:11:17,222
I'll call the police then.

189
00:11:17,737 --> 00:11:18,645
Hello?

190
00:11:18,725 --> 00:11:21,401
-Things are crazy over here!
-We'll scoop the poop!

191
00:11:21,921 --> 00:11:24,977
If we don't, the police
will come here, so just do it!

192
00:11:25,057 --> 00:11:26,908
But, I've got a weak stomach!

193
00:11:50,712 --> 00:11:53,583
Why did you have to order the
tenderloin special and raw meat plate?

194
00:11:53,663 --> 00:11:54,903
I can hear you.

195
00:11:54,983 --> 00:11:57,805
And I'm sure you ate much
more than I did.

196
00:11:58,023 --> 00:12:01,068
If I knew you were broke, I would've
settled for the vegetable bibimbap!

197
00:12:01,148 --> 00:12:03,925
You ordered
an extra bowl of cold noodles!

198
00:12:04,005 --> 00:12:07,410
If you didn't order that,
we'd be scooping five dollars less.

199
00:12:07,806 --> 00:12:09,347
Why are you changing the story now?

200
00:12:09,634 --> 00:12:11,644
You told me that I could order that!

201
00:12:11,725 --> 00:12:13,625
Just get back to cleaning the poop.

202
00:12:14,744 --> 00:12:17,304
If we stuck with the bibimbap,
we wouldn't be going through this.

203
00:12:17,398 --> 00:12:19,051
Again, I can hear you.

204
00:12:27,982 --> 00:12:29,500
Cow poop!

205
00:12:30,281 --> 00:12:31,554
Cow poop.

206
00:12:33,835 --> 00:12:35,108
Are you okay?

207
00:12:35,188 --> 00:12:36,874
Do I look okay to you?

208
00:12:36,954 --> 00:12:37,916
Gosh!

209
00:12:38,917 --> 00:12:39,995
I can't do this!

210
00:12:40,739 --> 00:12:41,740
The ma'am, the ma'am!

211
00:12:41,820 --> 00:12:43,298
We should pick up the pace.

212
00:13:00,753 --> 00:13:03,092
How much poop is 40 dollars' worth?

213
00:13:08,472 --> 00:13:09,358
These are good.

214
00:13:09,438 --> 00:13:10,774
They're plump and tasty.

215
00:13:10,854 --> 00:13:12,035
Thank you for the food!

216
00:13:12,115 --> 00:13:13,344
I'm going to eat all of it by myself.

217
00:13:13,424 --> 00:13:14,606
You're eating it all again?

218
00:13:16,984 --> 00:13:19,365
Of the countless things
we can eat in this world,

219
00:13:19,445 --> 00:13:21,365
why are we eating this kind of meat?

220
00:13:21,898 --> 00:13:25,179
You don't know
how great this tastes, do you?

221
00:13:26,851 --> 00:13:29,200
-Try it, it's delicious.
-That's disgusting!

222
00:13:29,377 --> 00:13:31,236
I feel like politely refusing.

223
00:13:31,316 --> 00:13:33,644
Put aside your reservations,
and just try it once.

224
00:13:33,724 --> 00:13:34,720
Disgusting.

225
00:13:34,800 --> 00:13:36,140
-Open wide.
-This is wrong.

226
00:13:37,953 --> 00:13:41,992
She really enjoyed
eating this disgusting thing.

227
00:13:48,742 --> 00:13:49,709
Forget this!

228
00:13:50,296 --> 00:13:52,443
-What are you doing?
-Lunatic.

229
00:13:52,523 --> 00:13:53,557
Are you crazy?

230
00:13:53,637 --> 00:13:55,848
It touched the fish cake!
I really wanted the fish cake!

231
00:13:56,020 --> 00:13:57,848
You just want to eat everything yourself.

232
00:13:58,902 --> 00:14:00,976
What are you doing?

233
00:14:11,707 --> 00:14:12,730
Over there.

234
00:14:12,810 --> 00:14:13,755
There?

235
00:14:14,084 --> 00:14:15,740
Enjoy!

236
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:22,410
Come here, baby!

237
00:14:23,218 --> 00:14:24,716
Dig in!

238
00:14:25,098 --> 00:14:26,618
Eat a lot!

239
00:14:28,494 --> 00:14:30,089
This is so much poop!

240
00:14:30,341 --> 00:14:32,666
-This has to go up there!
-Stop, stop, stop.

241
00:14:35,999 --> 00:14:37,199
A little more.

242
00:14:42,432 --> 00:14:43,467
We're done.

243
00:14:43,776 --> 00:14:44,835
Here.

244
00:14:46,406 --> 00:14:48,345
I dragged it all the way here,
so you bring it back.

245
00:14:48,425 --> 00:14:49,375
What?

246
00:14:50,592 --> 00:14:51,860
Seriously?

247
00:15:06,273 --> 00:15:09,666
Why don't we keep this experience
between us?

248
00:15:11,036 --> 00:15:12,080
Why?

249
00:15:12,361 --> 00:15:14,462
What's wrong with scooping cow poop?

250
00:15:16,840 --> 00:15:18,950
Scooping poop because we
couldn't pay for the tab...

251
00:15:19,252 --> 00:15:22,027
...is nothing to brag about.

252
00:15:24,628 --> 00:15:25,508
Okay.

253
00:15:25,588 --> 00:15:28,346
If it bothers you that much,
we'll keep it a secret.

254
00:15:47,305 --> 00:15:49,207
You've finally worked enough
to pay your tab.

255
00:15:50,071 --> 00:15:51,450
You can wash up over there.

256
00:15:51,694 --> 00:15:52,599
Yes.

257
00:15:56,611 --> 00:15:57,544
What?

258
00:15:57,862 --> 00:15:58,807
My name badge!

259
00:15:59,352 --> 00:16:00,553
Where did it go?

260
00:16:00,633 --> 00:16:02,192
I had it just moments ago!

261
00:16:02,438 --> 00:16:03,490
You lost your badge?

262
00:16:03,570 --> 00:16:05,756
Yes. Where did I drop it?

263
00:16:06,112 --> 00:16:09,131
So, why did you have to wear it
everywhere?

264
00:16:09,724 --> 00:16:10,663
Forget it.

265
00:16:10,743 --> 00:16:12,765
We don't have time,
so we'll need to wash up and get going.

266
00:16:12,845 --> 00:16:15,275
I really need my company badge!

267
00:16:15,815 --> 00:16:19,531
You can always have
another one issued to you.

268
00:16:19,611 --> 00:16:22,105
Let's get going.
We've lost enough time already.

269
00:16:22,670 --> 00:16:26,233
It may not be important to you,
but it's important to me.

270
00:16:26,525 --> 00:16:29,304
I can't leave it buried
under a mound of poop.

271
00:16:30,368 --> 00:16:33,316
After I wash, I'm leaving
in 20 minutes, no matter what!

272
00:16:36,704 --> 00:16:38,055
Gosh...

273
00:16:43,971 --> 00:16:46,212
Seriously. Where did it go?

274
00:16:52,390 --> 00:16:54,806
My badge, my badge.

275
00:16:59,372 --> 00:17:01,208
My badge.

276
00:17:18,804 --> 00:17:19,945
My badge!

277
00:17:20,202 --> 00:17:21,402
Where did you find it?

278
00:17:21,790 --> 00:17:23,060
I found it on the ground.

279
00:17:23,140 --> 00:17:24,073
Where on the ground?

280
00:17:24,153 --> 00:17:25,902
I looked everywhere for it!

281
00:17:25,982 --> 00:17:27,550
Are you sure you were
searching carefully?

282
00:17:27,630 --> 00:17:29,190
I found it on the ground in plain view.

283
00:17:30,085 --> 00:17:31,312
I'm so relieved.

284
00:17:31,825 --> 00:17:34,409
Thank you very much.

285
00:17:41,105 --> 00:17:42,740
I wouldn't kiss that.

286
00:17:43,792 --> 00:17:45,008
-Let's go now.
-Okay.

287
00:17:45,088 --> 00:17:46,431
Hey, young man!

288
00:17:46,996 --> 00:17:48,786
What happened to the compost pile?

289
00:17:49,079 --> 00:17:53,155
Did you dig through all of that manure?

290
00:17:55,936 --> 00:17:58,509
Did you really dig through
all of that cow poop?

291
00:17:58,926 --> 00:18:00,385
To find this for me?

292
00:18:01,015 --> 00:18:02,123
What?

293
00:18:02,504 --> 00:18:04,425
I already told you that
I found it on the ground.

294
00:18:05,633 --> 00:18:06,917
These flies.

295
00:18:10,971 --> 00:18:12,755
-Goodbye!
-Bye.

296
00:18:12,994 --> 00:18:13,937
See you around.

297
00:18:16,795 --> 00:18:18,186
Did they lose some gold?

298
00:18:36,056 --> 00:18:37,843
This is my very first time.

299
00:18:38,749 --> 00:18:41,172
First time working for a great company...

300
00:18:41,612 --> 00:18:44,255
...and the first time
I've had my picture on anything.

301
00:18:46,263 --> 00:18:49,056
While I was job hunting,

302
00:18:49,136 --> 00:18:52,001
I used to envy people
who had work badges.

303
00:18:52,702 --> 00:18:54,837
So every time I look at my badge...

304
00:18:55,323 --> 00:19:01,283
...I'm thankful and it fills me with joy.

305
00:19:02,084 --> 00:19:05,038
It reminds me that there's
a place for me in this company.

306
00:19:05,118 --> 00:19:09,030
It's proof that
I'm a part of the company.

307
00:19:11,255 --> 00:19:15,415
I'm taking this work badge thing
a bit too far, aren't I?

308
00:19:17,333 --> 00:19:19,847
Yes, a bit too far.

309
00:19:20,472 --> 00:19:23,325
But I do understand to a certain degree.

310
00:19:24,364 --> 00:19:28,537
Everyone has a few things
that are precious...

311
00:19:29,178 --> 00:19:31,520
...which seem worthless to others.

312
00:19:32,487 --> 00:19:37,076
What kinds of things do you have?

313
00:19:39,169 --> 00:19:41,652
The thing you shattered the other day.

314
00:19:41,893 --> 00:19:42,830
What?

315
00:19:44,044 --> 00:19:46,181
What's this? What are you doing here?

316
00:19:51,441 --> 00:19:52,604
Oh, that.

317
00:19:56,336 --> 00:19:59,230
Why the hand?

318
00:20:13,469 --> 00:20:14,841
What are you doing right now?

319
00:20:16,706 --> 00:20:17,619
What?

320
00:20:17,699 --> 00:20:20,050
I'm asking you to repay me
for the shattered glass.

321
00:20:21,005 --> 00:20:21,967
What?

322
00:20:22,650 --> 00:20:24,761
My goodness.

323
00:20:24,948 --> 00:20:26,344
Oh, you don't have the money right now.

324
00:20:26,424 --> 00:20:27,559
Send it to me when we get back to Seoul.

325
00:20:27,639 --> 00:20:29,285
My account number is 0820492...

326
00:20:29,365 --> 00:20:30,921
Wait, wait.

327
00:20:31,350 --> 00:20:34,820
What was after 08204?

328
00:20:35,845 --> 00:20:38,229
You're too easy to take advantage of.

329
00:20:38,783 --> 00:20:41,657
Haven't you ever heard of a joke before?

330
00:20:41,958 --> 00:20:43,375
I'll pay you back!

331
00:20:43,455 --> 00:20:44,795
What was after 04?

332
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:46,959
Well, it cost me 1,000 dollars.

333
00:20:47,039 --> 00:20:48,932
Okay, I get the joke.

334
00:21:06,627 --> 00:21:07,710
Do we have time to be doing this?

335
00:21:07,790 --> 00:21:09,036
I told you that we're fine.

336
00:21:09,116 --> 00:21:10,701
He told us to take our time.

337
00:21:12,891 --> 00:21:15,197
Oh, my, this chair is dirty.

338
00:21:15,817 --> 00:21:16,887
This one, too.

339
00:21:16,967 --> 00:21:18,534
I think I'll have to sit next to you.

340
00:21:19,514 --> 00:21:20,623
Let's eat and get out of here.

341
00:21:20,703 --> 00:21:21,545
Okay.

342
00:21:21,625 --> 00:21:23,815
We're not going anywhere.

343
00:21:23,960 --> 00:21:28,524
First, I'll find the perfect moment
for the car to break down.

344
00:21:28,605 --> 00:21:30,185
What's the matter with my car?

345
00:21:30,265 --> 00:21:31,341
Why, why?

346
00:21:31,838 --> 00:21:34,039
Oh, no, I think my car broke down!

347
00:21:34,119 --> 00:21:35,222
It won't start?

348
00:21:35,302 --> 00:21:36,645
No, it's not starting.

349
00:21:37,961 --> 00:21:39,335
Do you have anything in here?

350
00:21:40,734 --> 00:21:42,014
This isn't working.

351
00:21:42,613 --> 00:21:44,977
Then, I act like I'm making
a call to the service centre.

352
00:21:45,057 --> 00:21:46,699
Is this the service centre?

353
00:21:46,779 --> 00:21:48,080
Our car broke down here.

354
00:21:48,887 --> 00:21:50,787
We're in the countryside.

355
00:21:50,867 --> 00:21:52,106
There are mountains here.

356
00:21:52,186 --> 00:21:54,063
And I can see rice fields all around me.

357
00:21:55,038 --> 00:21:56,626
There are also lots of foxtails.

358
00:21:57,206 --> 00:21:59,436
The sky is beautiful here.

359
00:22:01,581 --> 00:22:04,071
The sun will eventually go down.

360
00:22:05,207 --> 00:22:07,367
Oh, my, Joonwoo. Look at the stars.

361
00:22:07,447 --> 00:22:09,991
They're so pretty, aren't they?

362
00:22:12,769 --> 00:22:17,569
As we stargaze together,
naturally we'll...

363
00:22:21,588 --> 00:22:23,157
...kiss.

364
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:26,130
Then as of today, my boyfriend will be...

365
00:22:26,210 --> 00:22:28,274
...Kim Joonwoo, the son
of the Jinsung Group's chairman.

366
00:22:28,354 --> 00:22:32,034
And I'll be hitting the biggest
jackpot of my life!

367
00:22:34,457 --> 00:22:35,702
Why aren't you eating?

368
00:22:36,077 --> 00:22:38,554
Well, I am eating.

369
00:22:49,472 --> 00:22:52,872
Wow, it's the ocean!

370
00:22:57,217 --> 00:22:59,088
Right, we're here for work.

371
00:23:00,061 --> 00:23:01,401
Oh, this is nice.

372
00:23:03,372 --> 00:23:05,261
Oh, this is nice!

373
00:23:09,138 --> 00:23:10,223
Let's look around.

374
00:23:10,303 --> 00:23:12,947
Then I'd like to make
a phone call before we begin.

375
00:23:13,027 --> 00:23:15,657
If the other two is going to be late,
we need money for dinner.

376
00:23:15,737 --> 00:23:17,680
I'll need someone to wire us some money.

377
00:23:18,702 --> 00:23:22,722
But you're really going to
pay me back, right?

378
00:23:22,802 --> 00:23:24,302
Serious?

379
00:23:24,382 --> 00:23:27,286
I'll sign a promissory note then.
My goodness.

380
00:23:28,670 --> 00:23:31,452
You're pretty gullible yourself, Mr Ji.

381
00:23:31,532 --> 00:23:32,653
I was only kidding.

382
00:23:34,620 --> 00:23:35,853
Go ahead and make your call.

383
00:23:35,933 --> 00:23:36,922
Yes, sir.

384
00:23:41,970 --> 00:23:42,899
Yes, Hyejin.

385
00:23:43,211 --> 00:23:45,309
Do you want to have dinner
with me later tonight?

386
00:23:45,389 --> 00:23:46,306
Well...

387
00:23:46,886 --> 00:23:49,745
How about at 8 PM in Kangwon Province?

388
00:23:50,170 --> 00:23:51,241
Why Kangwon?

389
00:23:52,172 --> 00:23:54,345
Oh, you're on a business trip,
aren't you?

390
00:23:55,848 --> 00:23:57,012
Are you coming back tomorrow?

391
00:24:01,162 --> 00:24:03,705
Sungjoon, I'm getting another call.
I'll call you back.

392
00:24:03,933 --> 00:24:05,671
Yes, I'll call you
when I get back to Seoul.

393
00:24:05,751 --> 00:24:06,698
Yes.

394
00:24:11,472 --> 00:24:12,568
Hey, wife.

395
00:24:13,097 --> 00:24:15,269
You weren't getting your phone all day.

396
00:24:15,639 --> 00:24:16,720
I know.

397
00:24:18,089 --> 00:24:19,628
I was involved in some labour earlier.

398
00:24:19,907 --> 00:24:20,808
What are you talking about?

399
00:24:20,888 --> 00:24:22,837
I'll tell you when I get back to Seoul.

400
00:24:23,483 --> 00:24:25,478
Hari, I need to borrow some money.

401
00:24:25,776 --> 00:24:28,506
What?
Why do I feel like you're phishing me?

402
00:24:28,818 --> 00:24:32,404
We need money right now,
but I have no money in my account.

403
00:24:32,484 --> 00:24:33,879
Yes, okay. I'll send it right away.

404
00:24:33,959 --> 00:24:36,088
Oh, and I'll be back tomorrow.

405
00:24:36,168 --> 00:24:37,945
I got caught up
with a business trip at work.

406
00:24:38,270 --> 00:24:39,605
A business trip?

407
00:24:41,355 --> 00:24:42,345
With whom?

408
00:24:42,690 --> 00:24:44,035
Ji Sungjoon.

409
00:24:44,944 --> 00:24:46,126
Just the two of you?

410
00:24:46,406 --> 00:24:47,674
Well, as of now.

411
00:24:47,754 --> 00:24:49,758
But our teammates are joining us
later tonight.

412
00:24:50,243 --> 00:24:51,802
Oh, I see.

413
00:24:52,215 --> 00:24:53,255
Thanks!

414
00:24:53,335 --> 00:24:55,082
What? Yes.

415
00:24:56,036 --> 00:24:56,972
Sure.

416
00:25:08,423 --> 00:25:09,550
I think this belongs to you.

417
00:25:13,494 --> 00:25:15,268
Ahreum, aren't you going home?

418
00:25:15,348 --> 00:25:17,094
Go home? It's only 4 PM.

419
00:25:17,174 --> 00:25:18,095
What?

420
00:25:18,271 --> 00:25:19,387
It's only 4 PM?

421
00:25:20,138 --> 00:25:21,178
It really is.

422
00:25:21,709 --> 00:25:22,865
It's only 4:00.

423
00:25:23,889 --> 00:25:25,643
I thought it was about seven.

424
00:25:26,622 --> 00:25:27,728
Isn't time going so slow today?

425
00:25:27,808 --> 00:25:29,960
Good. If you're not busy,
you can do this for me.

426
00:25:30,040 --> 00:25:31,537
I'm going out for some fresh air.

427
00:25:31,859 --> 00:25:32,889
Hey!

428
00:25:33,707 --> 00:25:34,889
Why, that...

429
00:25:42,793 --> 00:25:44,522
Are you sure that you know the way?

430
00:25:44,602 --> 00:25:46,030
Why are we still in the countryside?

431
00:25:46,110 --> 00:25:47,556
I know the way.

432
00:25:47,636 --> 00:25:48,605
This is...

433
00:25:49,982 --> 00:25:50,990
...a shortcut.

434
00:25:51,070 --> 00:25:52,919
That's odd...

435
00:25:54,658 --> 00:25:56,612
Hey, you're sweating.

436
00:25:56,692 --> 00:25:57,928
-Are you okay?
-What?

437
00:25:58,263 --> 00:25:59,635
I'm totally...

438
00:26:00,944 --> 00:26:02,426
...not fine.

439
00:26:03,848 --> 00:26:04,872
Oh, no.

440
00:26:04,952 --> 00:26:07,229
I think something was wrong
with the fish I had earlier.

441
00:26:07,971 --> 00:26:08,900
What am I going to do?

442
00:26:08,980 --> 00:26:10,839
I need to use the restroom.

443
00:26:10,919 --> 00:26:11,987
You have indigestion?

444
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:13,881
Bathroom.

445
00:26:13,961 --> 00:26:15,983
Oh, no, I don't see
any bathrooms around here.

446
00:26:18,045 --> 00:26:19,502
I can't hold it much longer.

447
00:26:20,277 --> 00:26:21,414
I need a bathroom!

448
00:26:21,903 --> 00:26:23,503
-This is crazy!
-What am I going to do?

449
00:26:23,786 --> 00:26:25,800
Hey, hey! Isn't that a bathroom?

450
00:26:25,880 --> 00:26:27,319
Where, where?

451
00:26:27,399 --> 00:26:28,448
Yes, it is!

452
00:26:49,818 --> 00:26:51,670
I thought I was going to die.

453
00:26:52,662 --> 00:26:53,909
But...

454
00:26:54,328 --> 00:26:56,746
Why did this have to happen
in front of Kim Joonwoo?

455
00:26:58,872 --> 00:26:59,858
It's okay.

456
00:26:59,938 --> 00:27:01,150
You can handle this, Seol.

457
00:27:02,827 --> 00:27:03,977
What's this?

458
00:27:04,454 --> 00:27:05,776
Why is this happening?

459
00:27:08,875 --> 00:27:10,393
Han Seol, are you okay?

460
00:27:14,908 --> 00:27:18,008
Hey, can you give me some tissue?

461
00:27:18,608 --> 00:27:19,480
What?

462
00:27:20,789 --> 00:27:23,394
I need tissue, tissue.

463
00:27:23,917 --> 00:27:25,856
What? I can't hear you, speak louder.

464
00:27:25,936 --> 00:27:29,044
Give me some tissue!
There's no tissue here!

465
00:27:29,124 --> 00:27:30,799
Oh, tissue?

466
00:27:31,955 --> 00:27:34,027
It's all over now!

467
00:27:37,559 --> 00:27:39,007
No, it's okay.

468
00:27:39,087 --> 00:27:40,176
You can handle this, Seol.

469
00:27:40,256 --> 00:27:41,496
You can do it.

470
00:27:49,382 --> 00:27:50,334
Are you okay?

471
00:27:51,032 --> 00:27:53,585
It's only a natural
physiological phenomenon.

472
00:27:53,665 --> 00:27:54,524
Let's go.

473
00:27:54,604 --> 00:27:56,813
Since we're here,
I should use the restroom too.

474
00:28:00,777 --> 00:28:02,529
It's okay, you can manage this, Seol.

475
00:28:05,728 --> 00:28:07,118
You can't handle this!

476
00:28:07,913 --> 00:28:10,327
This is so humiliating! It's all over!

477
00:28:15,098 --> 00:28:16,772
Han Seol, are you okay?

478
00:28:16,852 --> 00:28:18,428
That was the smell of compost.

479
00:28:18,508 --> 00:28:20,256
Can't you see that
we're surrounded by it?

480
00:28:20,336 --> 00:28:22,455
You've got to know that!

481
00:28:24,015 --> 00:28:25,647
All right, let me help you get up.

482
00:28:25,727 --> 00:28:28,853
That wasn't me, it was the compost!

483
00:28:31,003 --> 00:28:32,867
Why? Does your leg hurt?

484
00:28:32,947 --> 00:28:34,025
Yes.

485
00:28:38,468 --> 00:28:39,772
You've sprained it really badly.

486
00:28:40,000 --> 00:28:41,378
Do you think you can still drive?

487
00:28:41,599 --> 00:28:43,465
No, I can't. You'll have to drive.

488
00:28:43,700 --> 00:28:44,783
I don't have a license.

489
00:28:44,863 --> 00:28:45,791
What?

490
00:28:46,526 --> 00:28:49,309
Why isn't my little sister
getting her phone?

491
00:28:55,498 --> 00:28:56,633
Yes, Kim Joonwoo.

492
00:28:56,922 --> 00:28:59,159
How's the location hunt coming along?

493
00:28:59,239 --> 00:29:00,290
It's an emergency.

494
00:29:00,370 --> 00:29:02,880
We're barely halfway there,
and we're stranded.

495
00:29:02,960 --> 00:29:03,960
What?

496
00:29:04,040 --> 00:29:06,103
Han Seol sprained her leg,
so she can't drive.

497
00:29:06,183 --> 00:29:07,346
And I don't have a license.

498
00:29:07,426 --> 00:29:08,626
Hey, what about Jackson?

499
00:29:09,294 --> 00:29:10,718
I mean, Hyejin.

500
00:29:10,798 --> 00:29:12,851
She's gone ahead with the deputy chief.

501
00:29:13,211 --> 00:29:14,373
Hey, hey.

502
00:29:14,453 --> 00:29:16,060
Turn around. I've got the runs again.

503
00:29:17,830 --> 00:29:19,034
Hey, let go of me!

504
00:29:19,863 --> 00:29:22,257
-Hey, I've got to go.
-Hurry! Hurry!

505
00:29:22,798 --> 00:29:25,242
Hey, Kim Joonwoo. Hey, you!

506
00:29:28,688 --> 00:29:29,678
Wait.

507
00:29:30,102 --> 00:29:35,065
Does that mean Jackson is alone with him?

508
00:29:35,534 --> 00:29:38,151
This is an overnight business trip.

509
00:29:47,681 --> 00:29:48,861
Mr Ji.

510
00:29:49,404 --> 00:29:52,391
We can see the lighthouse from here,
so isn't this place perfect?

511
00:29:52,471 --> 00:29:54,721
It's also perfect for our theme
of vacationing alone.

512
00:29:55,089 --> 00:29:56,004
I guess so.

513
00:29:56,930 --> 00:29:57,908
It's not bad.

514
00:30:02,372 --> 00:30:05,237
Do you draft the plans yourself?

515
00:30:05,317 --> 00:30:07,638
Yes, well whatever comes into my head.

516
00:30:08,097 --> 00:30:09,468
That's really cool.

517
00:30:22,265 --> 00:30:24,780
I'm thinking about monotone colours.

518
00:30:25,125 --> 00:30:28,649
We want to portray the loneliness
while vacationing alone.

519
00:30:29,416 --> 00:30:32,726
We should also include a lamp
and some letterheads on the table.

520
00:30:33,955 --> 00:30:34,838
Letterheads?

521
00:30:34,918 --> 00:30:36,431
Even if you come here alone...

522
00:30:36,518 --> 00:30:40,176
...you'd want to write about it
and tell someone.

523
00:30:40,753 --> 00:30:42,745
And sometimes you
feel like sending a letter...

524
00:30:42,825 --> 00:30:45,037
...instead of making a phone call.

525
00:30:45,730 --> 00:30:49,066
I'm sure the person would
rather be here at the ocean...

526
00:30:49,146 --> 00:30:50,771
...with someone special.

527
00:30:51,405 --> 00:30:54,070
So this person might
light a bonfire alone...

528
00:30:54,657 --> 00:30:56,724
...drink some warm tea...

529
00:30:57,070 --> 00:30:59,090
...and maybe take a few Polaroid pictures.

530
00:30:59,530 --> 00:31:01,940
The person would probably
have a great time.

531
00:31:02,561 --> 00:31:07,332
Because he wants to tell that special...

532
00:31:07,783 --> 00:31:09,885
...someone that this is a great place...

533
00:31:10,105 --> 00:31:13,698
...and that they should come together
next time.

534
00:31:14,626 --> 00:31:19,104
Portraying letters and postcards
would change the theme...

535
00:31:19,618 --> 00:31:24,406
...from loneliness to one of anticipation.

536
00:31:31,810 --> 00:31:33,293
Oh, I'm sorry.

537
00:31:33,784 --> 00:31:35,065
I think I took it too far again.

538
00:31:35,303 --> 00:31:37,015
