I've experienced that before.

540
00:31:44,916 --> 00:31:46,553
Anticipating letters.

541
00:31:50,694 --> 00:31:52,112
What are you going to do
with all that bread?

542
00:31:52,192 --> 00:31:53,672
You're not going to eat
all these, are you?

543
00:31:53,752 --> 00:31:54,945
What? You're going to cry?

544
00:31:55,453 --> 00:31:56,651
Come on, cry!

545
00:31:56,732 --> 00:31:57,924
Come on, come on.

546
00:31:59,138 --> 00:32:00,739
When I moved overseas as a kid...

547
00:32:01,403 --> 00:32:03,819
...I couldn't speak the language
and I had no friends.

548
00:32:04,563 --> 00:32:08,040
But I had a friend who would
send me letters from Korea.

549
00:32:11,739 --> 00:32:13,838
I wanted to tell her
that I was doing well...

550
00:32:14,994 --> 00:32:16,679
...and that I was adjusting well.

551
00:32:17,729 --> 00:32:24,144
I think she gave me the courage
to stay strong and survive.

552
00:32:29,974 --> 00:32:32,978
Although, when the letters
stopped arriving...

553
00:32:33,704 --> 00:32:35,515
...I was a bit heartbroken.

554
00:32:41,176 --> 00:32:42,511
I see.

555
00:32:42,996 --> 00:32:46,514
Anyway, I guess we'll end up
with a warmer feature article.

556
00:32:48,439 --> 00:32:49,472
Good idea!

557
00:32:58,472 --> 00:33:00,173
I should finish up the sketches.

558
00:33:05,188 --> 00:33:07,069
Are there any better locations?

559
00:33:14,690 --> 00:33:15,838
How do you do?

560
00:33:15,918 --> 00:33:17,894
Your dog is so pretty! How old is he?

561
00:33:17,974 --> 00:33:19,126
He's three years old.

562
00:33:19,856 --> 00:33:21,843
-What's his name?
-His name is Professor.

563
00:33:24,338 --> 00:33:25,438
So cute!

564
00:33:26,105 --> 00:33:28,180
Bye now!

565
00:33:29,057 --> 00:33:30,209
Bye.

566
00:33:57,444 --> 00:33:58,665
Yes, Ms. Cha.

567
00:33:59,364 --> 00:34:01,348
We've found a great location.

568
00:34:01,745 --> 00:34:04,658
I'll send you some photos
I took with my phone.

569
00:34:05,464 --> 00:34:06,405
All right!

570
00:34:07,038 --> 00:34:08,005
Kim Hyejin.

571
00:34:08,858 --> 00:34:10,951
Why don't we wrap things
up here and move on?

572
00:34:14,577 --> 00:34:16,343
Why are you looking at me like that?

573
00:34:16,888 --> 00:34:17,886
Is something on my face?

574
00:34:18,182 --> 00:34:19,148
No.

575
00:34:19,936 --> 00:34:22,439
It's just my first time.

576
00:34:22,885 --> 00:34:24,706
Your first time for what?

577
00:34:24,989 --> 00:34:28,067
It's the first time I heard you
call me by my name.

578
00:34:28,147 --> 00:34:30,330
You were always like,
"Look here, Support".

579
00:34:30,410 --> 00:34:33,142
I didn't always refer to you
as "Look here, Support"!

580
00:34:33,222 --> 00:34:34,204
Look here, Support.

581
00:34:34,284 --> 00:34:35,193
Look here, Support.

582
00:34:35,273 --> 00:34:36,674
Hey, look here, Support.

583
00:34:36,754 --> 00:34:37,593
Look here, Support.

584
00:34:37,673 --> 00:34:38,609
Look here, Support.

585
00:34:38,689 --> 00:34:39,725
Look here, Support.

586
00:34:43,216 --> 00:34:46,886
Still, isn't that more appropriate
than Crazy Joon?

587
00:34:46,966 --> 00:34:49,903
-How do you feel about that?
-Pardon?

588
00:34:50,133 --> 00:34:51,766
That nickname is perfect for him,
Crazy Joon.

589
00:34:51,846 --> 00:34:54,435
Look here, you Crazy Joon...

590
00:34:54,797 --> 00:34:57,705
I wasn't the one who created
that nickname.

591
00:34:57,785 --> 00:34:59,022
Let's go have some dinner.

592
00:35:00,704 --> 00:35:01,805
Gosh.

593
00:35:03,317 --> 00:35:05,943
How can you call me Crazy Joon?

594
00:35:06,151 --> 00:35:07,235
You've got the wrong idea.

595
00:35:07,315 --> 00:35:08,927
It wasn't me who referred to you as that.

596
00:35:09,007 --> 00:35:10,989
You can always pay back
that 1,000 dollars.

597
00:35:11,069 --> 00:35:13,859
What? That has nothing to do with this.

598
00:35:14,116 --> 00:35:15,834
How can you call me Crazy Joon?

599
00:35:15,914 --> 00:35:17,022
I told you, it wasn't me!

600
00:35:22,397 --> 00:35:23,537
What are you doing?

601
00:35:24,470 --> 00:35:26,068
I don't eat peas.

602
00:35:32,544 --> 00:35:36,381
It doesn't taste very good
and it's all mushy.

603
00:35:36,461 --> 00:35:38,166
I don't know why people eat it.

604
00:35:41,117 --> 00:35:42,288
Why are you laughing?

605
00:35:42,666 --> 00:35:44,751
You just reminded me of someone.

606
00:35:47,581 --> 00:35:49,123
Oh, it's a Rubik's cube.

607
00:35:54,938 --> 00:35:56,707
Oh, my. I solved it!

608
00:35:57,210 --> 00:35:58,964
I solved it! I must be a genius.

609
00:36:00,343 --> 00:36:02,160
You've only solved one side.

610
00:36:03,257 --> 00:36:05,080
Let me see that. I'll solve it for you.

611
00:36:05,720 --> 00:36:07,892
I only need 30 seconds.

612
00:36:11,076 --> 00:36:12,865
Wow, you're fast!

613
00:36:17,130 --> 00:36:18,317
It's not working.

614
00:36:18,655 --> 00:36:20,611
What was that? This takes brains...

615
00:36:20,691 --> 00:36:23,546
...but I guess you're
not some genius, either.

616
00:36:23,626 --> 00:36:26,194
I'm good at anything that takes brains!

617
00:36:26,274 --> 00:36:29,329
You know, the video game
where you stack blocks...

618
00:36:29,588 --> 00:36:30,983
What was the name of that game?

619
00:36:34,172 --> 00:36:36,185
-That, right?
-Yes, that! The name was...

620
00:36:37,690 --> 00:36:38,783
-Tetris!
-Tetris!

621
00:36:40,383 --> 00:36:43,824
It takes me a tenth of a second
to drop each block.

622
00:36:43,904 --> 00:36:47,009
I think so fast,
that you can hardly keep up.

623
00:36:47,089 --> 00:36:49,915
And you've got
the wrong jingle for Tetris.

624
00:36:55,016 --> 00:36:56,696
That's the main melody.

625
00:36:56,776 --> 00:36:59,077
No, it's not! Tetris goes...

626
00:37:04,907 --> 00:37:06,379
You're completely wrong.

627
00:37:06,459 --> 00:37:08,555
You have a knack for arguing, Kim Hyejin.

628
00:37:08,856 --> 00:37:10,355
You're wrong, I tell you!

629
00:37:12,633 --> 00:37:13,779
Did you like girl groups?

630
00:37:13,859 --> 00:37:14,951
Of course I did!

631
00:37:15,031 --> 00:37:16,105
One, two, three!

632
00:37:16,185 --> 00:37:17,236
-SES!
-SES!

633
00:37:18,635 --> 00:37:19,849
Which SES member?

634
00:37:19,929 --> 00:37:20,956
-One, two, three.
-One, two, three.

635
00:37:21,036 --> 00:37:22,050
Did you watch dramas?

636
00:37:22,130 --> 00:37:23,206
Yes, I did.

637
00:37:23,286 --> 00:37:24,458
What did you like to watch?

638
00:37:24,736 --> 00:37:26,257
-Star in my Heart!
-Star in my Heart!

639
00:37:26,760 --> 00:37:28,171
-That's amazing!
-My goodness.

640
00:37:29,884 --> 00:37:32,478
-Looking here and there.
-Michael.

641
00:37:33,177 --> 00:37:34,883
You have the same hairstyle.

642
00:37:35,471 --> 00:37:38,075
If you are the same age as me,
I bet you know this very well.

643
00:37:38,160 --> 00:37:40,469
-The one with pointy hair...
-I know.

644
00:37:41,550 --> 00:37:46,168
I'm really sorry,
but we're closing for the night.

645
00:37:46,560 --> 00:37:47,580
Oh, really?

646
00:37:50,105 --> 00:37:51,831
Wow, look at the time.

647
00:37:55,345 --> 00:37:57,531
We were here for a long time.

648
00:37:57,611 --> 00:37:58,697
Yes.

649
00:38:01,100 --> 00:38:02,660
-Should we get going?
-Yes, of course.

650
00:38:13,799 --> 00:38:14,890
I'm so sorry.

651
00:38:22,175 --> 00:38:25,454
Are you still sick?

652
00:38:25,688 --> 00:38:26,792
No, I'm fine.

653
00:38:27,138 --> 00:38:28,786
I think something
got caught in my throat.

654
00:38:37,820 --> 00:38:40,454
I forgot to thank you for that.

655
00:38:42,886 --> 00:38:44,398
Thank you for that day.

656
00:38:45,769 --> 00:38:47,096
It's going to be okay.

657
00:38:47,606 --> 00:38:48,680
It's okay.

658
00:38:49,197 --> 00:38:50,562
Nothing's going to happen.

659
00:38:51,436 --> 00:38:53,764
Yes, well.

660
00:39:00,872 --> 00:39:02,612
My mother died...

661
00:39:03,775 --> 00:39:05,638
...when I was 12.

662
00:39:06,501 --> 00:39:08,958
She was in a car accident on a rainy day.

663
00:39:10,637 --> 00:39:13,083
Mum.

664
00:39:13,163 --> 00:39:15,768
Ever since that day,
I had a hard time driving in the rain.

665
00:39:16,193 --> 00:39:18,359
I keep getting the feeling...

666
00:39:18,682 --> 00:39:21,612
...that I'll be in the same
kind of accident.

667
00:39:21,692 --> 00:39:23,362
I was doing fine for a while...

668
00:39:24,232 --> 00:39:27,210
...but I don't know
what happened that day.

669
00:39:29,138 --> 00:39:32,039
But why am I talking about this?

670
00:39:32,948 --> 00:39:35,905
Was there whiskey in my dessert?

671
00:39:57,690 --> 00:39:58,895
Wow!

672
00:40:01,561 --> 00:40:04,457
I wish I could take half
of this back to Seoul.

673
00:40:11,143 --> 00:40:15,036
I thought you had become
a completely different person.

674
00:40:16,579 --> 00:40:21,499
I thought my gentle, pudgy
friend Sungjoon disappeared forever.

675
00:40:23,095 --> 00:40:26,258
But you're still the same.

676
00:40:27,169 --> 00:40:30,124
If I didn't hide from you like a fool,

677
00:40:30,423 --> 00:40:32,958
we'd be laughing comfortably
together like right now.

678
00:40:33,116 --> 00:40:35,921
And I'd be there for you
during your difficult times.

679
00:40:37,569 --> 00:40:38,750
Sungjoon!

680
00:40:41,046 --> 00:40:42,655
Today...

681
00:40:43,278 --> 00:40:47,928
...I think I could come clean today.

682
00:40:49,137 --> 00:40:52,228
That I'm your friend, Kim Hyejin.

683
00:40:52,764 --> 00:40:54,704
I think I can tell you everything...

684
00:40:55,990 --> 00:40:59,211
on a day like today.

685
00:41:06,830 --> 00:41:08,052
Yes, Mr Ji.

686
00:41:09,846 --> 00:41:12,287
I don't think she can drive right now.

687
00:41:13,587 --> 00:41:14,825
Yes, I'm sorry.

688
00:41:15,441 --> 00:41:16,947
I'll see you back at the company.

689
00:41:17,740 --> 00:41:18,790
Yes, sir.

690
00:41:24,055 --> 00:41:25,763
That was the smell of compost.

691
00:41:25,843 --> 00:41:27,502
Can't you see that
we're surrounded by it?

692
00:41:27,582 --> 00:41:29,871
You've got to know that!

693
00:41:31,126 --> 00:41:32,292
Hey, hey.

694
00:41:32,372 --> 00:41:35,999
Turn around. I've got the runs again...

695
00:41:39,126 --> 00:41:40,543
She's kind of cute.

696
00:41:41,506 --> 00:41:44,211
I'm done for! My life is over!

697
00:41:44,291 --> 00:41:46,046
Ouch!

698
00:41:47,719 --> 00:41:49,410
It's all over.

699
00:41:49,490 --> 00:41:50,846
I'm done for.

700
00:41:59,195 --> 00:42:05,995
I'm about to tell you something
that might surprise you.

701
00:42:06,602 --> 00:42:08,691
Have you ever heard that...

702
00:42:09,892 --> 00:42:15,324
...some memories
are best kept in the past.

703
00:42:17,167 --> 00:42:21,637
And that memories are most beautiful
when they're reminisced?

704
00:42:23,834 --> 00:42:26,631
I felt that way until recently.

705
00:42:28,288 --> 00:42:29,369
But today...

706
00:42:31,812 --> 00:42:34,806
...I realized
that it might not be the case.

707
00:42:40,294 --> 00:42:42,845
Kim Hyejin,
what are you trying to tell me?

708
00:42:42,925 --> 00:42:44,155
Mr Ji.

709
00:42:56,702 --> 00:42:58,830
-To be honest...
-Hey, Sister!

710
00:42:59,649 --> 00:43:01,239
You owe me sea snails!

711
00:43:01,319 --> 00:43:04,863
I, Kim Hyejin, promise to grant
Kim Shinhyuk three favours!

712
00:43:04,943 --> 00:43:07,918
See, you've made me a promise!

713
00:43:07,998 --> 00:43:10,885
Are you trying to back out of our deal?

714
00:43:11,455 --> 00:43:12,856
What sea snails?

715
00:43:13,482 --> 00:43:17,191
Who comes all the way
to Kangwon Province for sea snails?

716
00:43:17,637 --> 00:43:18,766
Me.

717
00:43:19,984 --> 00:43:21,123
I'm kidding.

718
00:43:21,203 --> 00:43:24,231
Joonwoo couldn't make it,
so I'm filling in for him.

719
00:43:24,311 --> 00:43:27,483
I thought you might need help
hunting for a location.

720
00:43:28,474 --> 00:43:30,834
I didn't know that you work so hard.

721
00:43:31,618 --> 00:43:32,790
Let's go inside.

722
00:43:33,028 --> 00:43:36,523
Since I just got here, we should
have a drink before we call it a night!

723
00:43:36,774 --> 00:43:37,885
I don't drink.

724
00:43:39,283 --> 00:43:40,597
Then go on ahead.

725
00:43:40,677 --> 00:43:42,635
-We'll go after we've had a drink.
-What?

726
00:43:42,715 --> 00:43:44,781
Let's go.
They have non-alcoholic beer these days.

727
00:43:47,536 --> 00:43:49,574
Why did you come here?

728
00:43:49,654 --> 00:43:50,845
Why do you think?

729
00:43:51,401 --> 00:43:52,751
Let's go, Little Sister.

730
00:43:54,992 --> 00:43:59,021
Hey, it's nice to be away from the city!

731
00:44:00,970 --> 00:44:03,205
But since I came here in such a hurry...

732
00:44:03,285 --> 00:44:05,441
...I didn't pack any underwear.

733
00:44:05,818 --> 00:44:08,156
Do you have any underwear
that I can borrow?

734
00:44:10,116 --> 00:44:11,490
Did you leave yours with me?

735
00:44:11,976 --> 00:44:13,475
I'm not an underwear merchant...

736
00:44:13,555 --> 00:44:15,680
...so stop talking
about underwear with me!

737
00:44:16,528 --> 00:44:17,820
I've only brought my own.

738
00:44:18,091 --> 00:44:20,925
Then do I have to wash mine and dry them?

739
00:44:21,153 --> 00:44:24,472
I usually sleep in my underwear.

740
00:44:24,552 --> 00:44:27,561
If I have to wash them,
where will that put me?

741
00:44:29,876 --> 00:44:31,184
I'm so sorry.

742
00:44:31,264 --> 00:44:32,620
Goodness.

743
00:44:33,412 --> 00:44:36,056
Buy a pair at the convenience store.

744
00:44:36,136 --> 00:44:37,863
You're definitely a brain.

745
00:44:38,158 --> 00:44:40,753
Why didn't I think of that?

746
00:44:40,833 --> 00:44:43,714
Hyejin, let me open that for you.

747
00:44:43,794 --> 00:44:45,037
Since I'm your older brother.

748
00:44:45,234 --> 00:44:47,794
This is how you open this.

749
00:44:55,148 --> 00:44:58,123
Outside the company,
we've agreed to be siblings.

750
00:44:58,203 --> 00:44:59,606
Right, Hyejin?

751
00:45:00,424 --> 00:45:02,362
Oh, brother and sister?

752
00:45:03,923 --> 00:45:05,555
That's not alcohol-free.

753
00:45:07,337 --> 00:45:12,919
Kim Hyejin likes to be
friendly with everyone.

754
00:45:13,087 --> 00:45:14,788
No, it's not like that...

755
00:45:14,868 --> 00:45:17,323
Little Sister, wait a second.

756
00:45:18,376 --> 00:45:19,695
There's something on your face.

757
00:45:20,716 --> 00:45:22,134
There, it's gone.

758
00:45:23,238 --> 00:45:26,101
I brought you a gift from Seoul.

759
00:45:26,181 --> 00:45:27,202
A gift.

760
00:45:35,646 --> 00:45:39,257
Yes! That's the reaction
I was waiting for!

761
00:45:39,337 --> 00:45:40,456
Am I right?

762
00:45:41,378 --> 00:45:42,522
Seriously!

763
00:45:42,706 --> 00:45:46,369
I thought it was a real bug!

764
00:45:50,472 --> 00:45:51,947
There was a mosquito buzzing around.

765
00:45:52,599 --> 00:45:53,914
Mosquitoes in the fall?

766
00:45:56,253 --> 00:45:59,164
Hey, that didn't feel so good.

767
00:46:02,506 --> 00:46:04,111
You look really creepy.

768
00:46:04,191 --> 00:46:05,180
What?

769
00:46:07,343 --> 00:46:09,705
Greasy and creepy...

770
00:46:18,384 --> 00:46:19,371
Hurry.

771
00:46:31,060 --> 00:46:33,998
How does someone get drunk so quickly?

772
00:46:34,483 --> 00:46:36,412
I can't tell whether he's drunk or not.

773
00:46:36,980 --> 00:46:39,013
That was tiring.
Jackson, get me a cup of water.

774
00:46:39,093 --> 00:46:40,418
Go and get it yourself.

775
00:46:41,463 --> 00:46:44,635
If you can't handle a single drink,
why did you insist on drinking?

776
00:46:44,885 --> 00:46:47,629
Aren't you going to get a cup
of water for your older brother?

777
00:46:47,709 --> 00:46:49,190
Are you going to act petty like this?

778
00:46:50,701 --> 00:46:56,129
Jackson, do you think I look creepy, too?

779
00:46:57,463 --> 00:46:58,537
No, right?

780
00:46:59,998 --> 00:47:01,457
I'll get you some water.

781
00:47:05,740 --> 00:47:06,899
What's wrong with my face?

782
00:47:07,094 --> 00:47:08,093
Tell me what?

783
00:47:08,173 --> 00:47:09,632
What? What is it?

784
00:47:11,271 --> 00:47:12,704
You startled me!

785
00:47:14,243 --> 00:47:17,627
You're so good looking,
I'm always surprised to see you.

786
00:47:19,743 --> 00:47:20,763
Hi.

787
00:47:21,357 --> 00:47:22,871
Shall I look through the pictures?

788
00:47:34,510 --> 00:47:35,910
There are a lot of great locations.

789
00:48:27,135 --> 00:48:29,272
I missed you, my friend.

790
00:48:30,293 --> 00:48:32,352
Hey, when did you get home?

791
00:48:32,432 --> 00:48:34,190
-Late last night.
-I see.

792
00:48:34,674 --> 00:48:37,560
Did anything happen
at your business trip?

793
00:48:37,640 --> 00:48:38,800
Happen? Like what?

794
00:48:39,654 --> 00:48:43,477
Was it awkward between
you and Ji Sungjoon?

795
00:48:44,610 --> 00:48:46,147
I thought it would be.

796
00:48:46,227 --> 00:48:48,882
But he's easy to get along
with outside of work.

797
00:48:49,962 --> 00:48:51,112
I have to get going now.

798
00:48:51,587 --> 00:48:54,333
It's the week of deadlines,
so it'll be hard to see each other.

799
00:48:54,413 --> 00:48:56,729
Don't cry because I'm not here,
and don't wait up for me.

800
00:48:56,809 --> 00:48:57,809
Okay.

801
00:48:58,779 --> 00:49:00,846
Make sure that you feed yourself!

802
00:49:01,339 --> 00:49:02,211
Okay.

803
00:49:02,762 --> 00:49:04,672
Hey, you're going to fall! Stop running!

804
00:49:13,182 --> 00:49:15,639
Good morning, Kim Hyejin.

805
00:49:17,204 --> 00:49:18,184
Oh, yes.

806
00:49:18,264 --> 00:49:20,194
Good morning, Mr Ji.

807
00:49:22,593 --> 00:49:24,626
-Good morning.
-How are you?

808
00:49:24,706 --> 00:49:25,998
Hello.

809
00:49:26,379 --> 00:49:29,541
Now, it's time for deadlines, so let's
all cooperate together and do well.

810
00:49:29,621 --> 00:49:30,543
Yes, sir.

811
00:49:30,623 --> 00:49:31,593
Let's do this!

812
00:49:31,673 --> 00:49:33,426
-Let's do it!
-Go for it!

813
00:49:38,675 --> 00:49:41,208
-What's wrong with Mr Ji?
-Is something wrong with him?

814
00:49:41,288 --> 00:49:43,405
His new attitude is starting to scare me.

815
00:49:48,065 --> 00:49:50,979
Hey, you're growing a beard!

816
00:49:51,059 --> 00:49:52,230
Looks good on you.

817
00:49:54,196 --> 00:49:57,432
Everyone, let's do this!

818
00:49:57,512 --> 00:49:59,475
-Yes!
-Yes!

819
00:50:04,108 --> 00:50:07,098
I think it's good, but it would be
better to take this bit out.

820
00:50:07,178 --> 00:50:08,321
Is this the only thing
that needs editing?

821
00:50:08,401 --> 00:50:10,010
-Yes.
-I understand.

822
00:50:13,793 --> 00:50:14,795
Yes, Hyejin.

823
00:50:15,424 --> 00:50:17,371
How was your business trip?

824
00:50:18,866 --> 00:50:21,185
I couldn't get a hold of you.

825
00:50:21,265 --> 00:50:23,586
Sorry, I've lost track of time.

826
00:50:24,324 --> 00:50:26,177
Mr Ji, the photographs
for the movie segment...

827
00:50:26,257 --> 00:50:27,267
Wait a moment.

828
00:50:27,347 --> 00:50:29,414
I have deadlines to meet,
so I'm a bit busy now.

829
00:50:29,494 --> 00:50:31,301
Sorry, I'll have to call you back.

830
00:50:32,183 --> 00:50:34,010
Sungjoon, Sungjoon.

831
00:50:55,502 --> 00:50:56,910
Thanks for lunch.

832
00:51:13,738 --> 00:51:15,098
I'm so tired.

833
00:51:22,766 --> 00:51:23,817
Hyejin.

834
00:51:26,756 --> 00:51:27,878
Hyejin.

835
00:51:28,370 --> 00:51:29,469
Get me the box.

836
00:51:29,549 --> 00:51:30,690
Yes, I understand.

837
00:51:33,080 --> 00:51:34,908
It's finished!

838
00:51:35,208 --> 00:51:37,092
I'm going to sleep until tomorrow.

839
00:51:37,172 --> 00:51:39,205
The person who wakes me will die.

840
00:51:39,285 --> 00:51:40,714
So stay away from me.

841
00:51:40,794 --> 00:51:42,756
I need some sleep.

842
00:51:51,389 --> 00:51:52,597
Have you arrived?

843
00:51:53,307 --> 00:51:54,895
Good work everyone.

844
00:51:55,564 --> 00:51:57,634
Hang in there a little longer.

845
00:51:57,849 --> 00:51:58,746
Pardon?

846
00:51:59,447 --> 00:52:04,670
The models for our anniversary edition
will be available this Thursday.

847
00:52:05,439 --> 00:52:08,774
They're top models,
so we have to accommodate their schedules.

848
00:52:09,077 --> 00:52:11,432
I'm going to lose it!

849
00:52:12,121 --> 00:52:13,343
Come on now.

850
00:52:13,423 --> 00:52:17,367
This is the final stretch,
so let's work hard and celebrate after.

851
00:52:19,243 --> 00:52:21,336
I should quit this job.

852
00:52:22,054 --> 00:52:23,213
I don't care about wealth
or honour anymore.

853
00:52:23,293 --> 00:52:24,227
Yes.

854
00:52:24,307 --> 00:52:25,562
What's going to be our makeup concept?

855
00:52:25,642 --> 00:52:26,646
-Yes.
-Is that so? Yes.

856
00:52:26,726 --> 00:52:28,405
Regarding the collaboration
with James Taylor...

857
00:52:28,485 --> 00:52:30,317
Let's schedule it for this Thursday.

858
00:52:31,390 --> 00:52:32,393
Yes.

859
00:52:34,471 --> 00:52:35,492
Yes.

860
00:52:39,380 --> 00:52:40,391
Yes?

861
00:52:44,247 --> 00:52:45,394
You have a delivery.

862
00:52:46,836 --> 00:52:47,863
Thank you.

863
00:52:48,452 --> 00:52:49,874
Well, Mr Ji.

864
00:52:50,623 --> 00:52:54,432
After the photo shoot on Thursday,
will you have some time?

865
00:52:55,319 --> 00:52:58,882
I can't pay you for the glass,
but I'd like to buy you dinner.

866
00:52:59,232 --> 00:53:01,728
And there's something
I'd like to tell you.

867
00:53:05,285 --> 00:53:06,158
All right then.

868
00:53:23,454 --> 00:53:27,349
Jackson, what were you
talking to Mr Ji about?

869
00:53:28,916 --> 00:53:31,533
I asked him if he had time
after the photo shoot on Thursday.

870
00:53:31,812 --> 00:53:33,689
I plan to tell him everything then.

871
00:53:34,360 --> 00:53:35,328
Really?

872
00:53:45,647 --> 00:53:47,192
Why are you looking at me like that?

873
00:53:49,788 --> 00:53:50,749
Oh, no.

874
00:53:53,204 --> 00:53:57,298
Do I remind you
of your little sister again?

875
00:53:57,378 --> 00:53:58,329
What?

876
00:54:00,708 --> 00:54:01,746
Yes.

877
00:54:02,350 --> 00:54:05,147
The more I look at you,
the more you start to resemble her.

878
00:54:06,040 --> 00:54:11,124
The way you can eat anything,
and the way you look at me.

879
00:54:12,955 --> 00:54:14,349
Go on and eat, Little Sister.

880
00:54:14,429 --> 00:54:15,417
Yes.

881
00:54:20,173 --> 00:54:21,339
That's hot!

882
00:54:25,206 --> 00:54:27,443
Now, you're exactly like her.

883
00:54:30,201 --> 00:54:31,217
Let's eat.

884
00:54:34,141 --> 00:54:37,649
Big Brother, have some more noodles.

885
00:54:40,049 --> 00:54:41,602
You don't have to do that.

886
00:54:42,408 --> 00:54:43,571
How much do I owe you?

887
00:54:43,651 --> 00:54:44,882
It'll be 20 dollars.

888
00:54:46,826 --> 00:54:49,174
Wow, that's so cute!

889
00:54:49,254 --> 00:54:50,552
Is that your dog?

890
00:54:50,632 --> 00:54:51,743
Yes, that's her.

891
00:54:51,823 --> 00:54:52,736
Coco.

892
00:54:53,252 --> 00:54:54,380
My younger sister.

893
00:54:55,163 --> 00:54:56,406
-Thank you, Aunt.
-Thank you.

894
00:54:56,486 --> 00:54:57,944
-Good night.
-Bye.

895
00:54:58,721 --> 00:55:00,363
Coco? Sister?

896
00:55:01,464 --> 00:55:02,703
Little Sister?

897
00:55:04,334 --> 00:55:07,508
Then are you comparing me to your dog?

898
00:55:08,085 --> 00:55:08,986
A dog?

899
00:55:09,066 --> 00:55:09,919
Yes, why?

900
00:55:09,999 --> 00:55:11,349
I thought she was your sister!

901
00:55:11,429 --> 00:55:13,721
Yes, my little sister.
She was a part of the family.

902
00:55:15,766 --> 00:55:18,758
You didn't think she was human, did you?

903
00:55:19,878 --> 00:55:22,290
You've had the wrong idea!

904
00:55:22,370 --> 00:55:24,850
You're completely confused.

905
00:55:26,803 --> 00:55:27,795
Why, you...

906
00:55:27,875 --> 00:55:28,833
Are you making fun of me?

907
00:55:28,913 --> 00:55:30,321
Come here!

908
00:55:30,768 --> 00:55:32,669
What's the matter?
I never said she's human.

909
00:55:32,749 --> 00:55:34,782
You want to get bitten by a woman
that looks like a dog?

910
00:55:34,862 --> 00:55:36,707
Coco never bit anyone! Don't bite me!

911
00:55:36,787 --> 00:55:38,771
Coco, my foot!
I'm going to bite your nose!

912
00:55:38,851 --> 00:55:41,518
I didn't do anything,
so why are you overreacting?

913
00:55:45,552 --> 00:55:49,999
You always joke around and tease me
and now you compare me to your dog?

914
00:55:50,447 --> 00:55:53,839
Why did I give you more noodles?

915
00:55:53,919 --> 00:55:55,222
About that...

916
00:55:55,535 --> 00:55:58,391
I felt sorry for you because
I thought that your sister died!

917
00:55:58,471 --> 00:56:01,142
I wanted to be good to you,
but this is going too far!

918
00:56:01,222 --> 00:56:02,781
How can you do this to me?

919
00:56:06,041 --> 00:56:08,815
Are you ignoring me like a dog now?

920
00:56:09,161 --> 00:56:12,154
Yes, that's all you think I am, a dog.

921
00:56:18,452 --> 00:56:19,874
That's why I said that.

922
00:56:20,712 --> 00:56:22,883
Yes, let's hear your reason!

923
00:56:22,963 --> 00:56:24,778
Why do you treat me like this? Why?

924
00:56:25,658 --> 00:56:26,717
Jackson,

925
00:56:27,393 --> 00:56:29,247
I think I have feelings for you.

926
00:56:31,406 --> 00:56:32,370
What?

927
00:56:32,450 --> 00:56:34,124
You told me that you're
coming clean with the chief editor.

928
00:56:34,204 --> 00:56:35,790
But for some reason, it bothered me.

929
00:56:36,362 --> 00:56:39,568
It bothers me to think that things
will go well between the two of you.

930
00:56:39,648 --> 00:56:41,923
And I keep thinking about you.

931
00:56:42,508 --> 00:56:44,178
I was wondering why I felt that way...

932
00:56:45,365 --> 00:56:46,687
...and now I think I know.

933
00:56:50,338 --> 00:56:52,217
I think I like you.

934
00:56:52,861 --> 00:56:54,087
A lot.

935
00:56:58,800 --> 00:56:59,930
Mr Kim.

936
00:57:00,736 --> 00:57:02,252
What are you talking about?

937
00:57:05,866 --> 00:57:08,244
I almost fell for it again!

938
00:57:08,324 --> 00:57:09,566
Your ridiculous lies!

939
00:57:09,646 --> 00:57:11,515
It's not a lie. I'm being sincere.

940
00:57:11,595 --> 00:57:13,513
I really have feelings for you.

941
00:57:13,593 --> 00:57:15,110
Yes, right!

942
00:57:15,435 --> 00:57:17,801
I'm not talking to you anymore!

943
00:57:19,268 --> 00:57:20,775
Seriously.

944
00:57:22,988 --> 00:57:24,063
Really?

945
00:57:26,323 --> 00:57:27,728
You can't do that to me!

946
00:57:30,195 --> 00:57:32,138
I've really fallen for her!

947
00:57:32,218 --> 00:57:34,169
I like her, even when she acts like that!

948
00:57:34,424 --> 00:57:35,463
Jackson!

949
00:57:35,760 --> 00:57:36,793
Hyejin.

950
00:57:36,873 --> 00:57:37,995
Kim Hyejin!

951
00:57:39,940 --> 00:57:41,963
How was the business trip?

952
00:57:42,274 --> 00:57:43,230
The business trip?

953
00:57:45,809 --> 00:57:47,723
It was rather odd this time around.

954
00:57:48,041 --> 00:57:49,488
Do you know what I did there?

955
00:57:49,661 --> 00:57:51,071
I scooped cow manure...

956
00:57:52,462 --> 00:57:54,702
I don't think the timing is right.
We've just had dinner.

957
00:57:55,438 --> 00:57:56,338
Why?

958
00:57:56,496 --> 00:57:57,990
Was it fun?

959
00:57:59,092 --> 00:58:00,573
No, I'll tell you about it next time.

960
00:58:01,692 --> 00:58:02,888
Why, what is it?

961
00:58:04,238 --> 00:58:08,025
We have an intern that shares your name.

962
00:58:08,105 --> 00:58:09,436
She's our age,

963
00:58:09,858 --> 00:58:13,092
but she remembers all of the arcade
jingles from back in the day.

964
00:58:13,172 --> 00:58:14,142
She's like...

965
00:58:15,454 --> 00:58:17,262
She was trying to imitate the song.

966
00:58:17,342 --> 00:58:18,744
It was so funny.

967
00:58:20,279 --> 00:58:21,327
Sungjoon.

968
00:58:21,407 --> 00:58:22,348
Yes?

969
00:58:24,408 --> 00:58:26,200
Can I ask you one thing?

970
00:58:27,851 --> 00:58:28,772
What is it?

971
00:58:29,110 --> 00:58:33,412
Are you meeting with me...

972
00:58:35,160 --> 00:58:36,640
...because I'm your childhood friend?

973
00:58:40,296 --> 00:58:42,881
What do you mean all of a sudden?

974
00:58:44,361 --> 00:58:45,289
I want to...

975
00:58:46,625 --> 00:58:48,133
...hear your answer.

976
00:58:50,833 --> 00:58:53,113
I want to know how you feel about me.

977
00:58:53,420 --> 00:58:54,612
And why...

978
00:58:56,473 --> 00:58:58,395
...you're meeting with me.

979
00:59:02,311 --> 00:59:05,931
Because I'm sure of my feelings.

980
00:59:11,046 --> 00:59:12,122
Hyejin.

981
00:59:15,159 --> 00:59:16,765
I'm warning you one last time.

982
00:59:16,845 --> 00:59:18,788
You can't treat me like that, okay?

983
00:59:19,123 --> 00:59:20,575
Okay, okay.

984
00:59:20,655 --> 00:59:21,784
I'm sorry.

985
00:59:22,137 --> 00:59:23,693
This is how I feel about you.

986
00:59:36,917 --> 00:59:38,412
As a token of my apology...

987
00:59:41,850 --> 00:59:46,465
Can you help me throw away
my shoe that doesn't fit?

988
00:59:46,545 --> 00:59:51,980
Sungjoon thinks that someone
other than me is his first love.

989
00:59:52,060 --> 00:59:55,684
I think I'm falling for him.

990
00:59:56,268 --> 00:59:57,566
My avatar.

991
00:59:57,646 --> 00:59:59,593
I shouldn't meet him.

992
01:00:01,097 --> 01:00:02,235
What the...

993
01:00:02,641 --> 01:00:03,636
What the what?

994
01:00:03,977 --> 01:00:05,541
So, what's the token of your apology?

995
01:00:06,148 --> 01:00:07,516
What do you keep looking at?

996
01:00:09,132 --> 01:00:10,548
What's the matter?

997
01:00:38,729 --> 01:00:42,918
I won't act in ways that
might make you concerned.

998
01:00:43,565 --> 01:00:45,349
What is it that you want to tell me?

999
01:00:45,429 --> 01:00:46,817
How much do you know
about your girlfriend?

1000
01:00:46,897 --> 01:00:50,146
I'll root for your love.

1001
01:00:50,494 --> 01:00:51,743
I'm sorry, Hyejin.

1002
01:00:51,823 --> 01:00:53,155
Please end this.

1003
01:00:53,514 --> 01:00:54,557
Pretending to be Kim Hyejin.

1004
01:00:54,637 --> 01:00:55,931
Then what are you?

1005
01:00:56,131 --> 01:00:57,818
I like her.

1006
01:00:58,294 --> 01:00:59,750
I like Kim Hyejin.

1007
01:01:00,573 --> 01:01:01,750
Who are you?

1008
01:01:02,015 --> 01:01:04,409
Who are you to keep
getting on my nerves?
